<h2><a>A quick look at the best hearing aids</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><strong>Most tech-forward hearing aids:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Starkey">Starkey Livio Edge AI</a></li><li><strong>Best invisible hearing aids:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Eargo">Eargo Neo HiFi</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Phonak-Lyric">Phonak Lyric</a></li><li><strong>Best Invisible hearing aids for mild hearing loss:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Nano">Nano CIC Invisible Hearing Aids</a></li><li><strong>Best hearing aids for natural sound:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Lively">Lively 2 Pro</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#ReSound">ReSound One</a></li><li><strong>Best low cost hearing aids:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Kirkland">Kirkland Signature 10.0 with Tcoil</a></li><li><strong>Best hearing aids for streaming:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Signia-Styletto">Signia Styletto Connect</a></li><li><strong>Best hearing aids for one-sided hearing loss:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Signia-CROS">Signia CROS Pure Charge&amp;Go X</a></li><li><strong>Best hearing aids for severe hearing loss:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Oticon-Xceed">Oticon Xceed</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Phonak-Bolero">Phonak Bolero Marvel</a></li><li><strong>Best hearing aids for tinnitus:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Oticon-More">Oticon More</a></li><li><strong>Best ready-to-wear hearing aids:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid#Signia-Silk">Signia Silk X</a></li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you’re thinking about getting hearing aids or looking into new ones, you’re not alone. Approximately&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nidcd.nih.gov/health/statistics/quick-statistics-hearing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">37.5 million U.S. adultsTrusted Source</a>&nbsp;have some degree of hearing loss. Many people with hearing loss may benefit from assistive technologies, such as hearing aids.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Shopping for hearing aids can be challenging, especially if you haven’t purchased them before. Some come with lots of options and settings, while others are simpler to use. We rounded up an array of options based on common concerns.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Note that before choosing the right hearing aids for you, it’s best to speak with your doctor or a healthcare professional and ask for a hearing assessment. They may refer you to a specialist and can help you decide if and what&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/types-of-hearing-aids">type of hearing aids</a>&nbsp;you might need.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>How we chose</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We only chose hearing aids from manufacturers with solid reputations. Hearing aids are medical devices that must meet criteria approved by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We read scores of online consumer reviews and spoke with people who use some of them. We only chose hearing aids that consistently get more positive than negative comments.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Most of the hearing aids on this list come with financing options, a manufacturer’s warranty, and a 30-day or greater risk-free trial.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We looked at a wide range of features that are important to consumers, including:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>invisibility, or being discreet to wear</li><li>Bluetooth connectivity</li><li>ease of use</li><li>adaptive noise reduction</li><li><a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/tinnitus">tinnitus</a>&nbsp;relief</li><li>custom fit options</li><li>price</li><li>ability to recharge</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Pricing guide</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Hearing aid prices can vary significantly from retailer to retailer. We’ve indicated the price for single hearing aids. In some instances, these prices are bundled and reflect additional services like follow-up visits and hearing aid maintenance.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Prices are estimated as follows:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><strong>$</strong>&nbsp;= under $1,000</li><li><strong>$$</strong>&nbsp;= $1,000–$2,000</li><li><strong>$$$</strong>&nbsp;= over $2,000</li></ul>
